Exploring Household Appliance Usage Patterns

👀Overview of the Data

This data set records the usage of household appliances in four time periods that are more in line with my own living conditions. It includes the total time the device is used, the type of device used, and the time when the usage is recorded. I want to use this data to understand which time period of the day I spend more time at home, so that I can understand my living conditions and infer whether I go to bed early and go to class during the day, as well as the electricity usage to verify the electricity bill I pay for rent every time.

A picture of home appliances

⏲️Total Electricity Consumption by Time Period

It can be seen that the afternoon and evening are the periods when electricity consumption is the highest, because I stay at home the longest during these two periods. There are fewer classes in the afternoon and classes may end late in the morning, so I stay at home in the afternoon, and use electrical appliances at night when cooking. Midnight is the shortest period because I sleep most of the time, so I only use electrical appliances when I stay up late.

Bar chart showing total hours of appliances use by time period. Afternoon and Evening have the highest usage.

💻Which Appliances Are Used Most?

This shows that the computer and TV are used most frequently. The computer is used most at home because I use it to do homework, etc. The TV is often turned on to play TV series, etc. The water heater is used every day, but it is not the highest because I use it every day but not often. Sometimes I wash my hair for 40 minutes, and sometimes I don’t wash my hair for less than 20 minutes. So even if there are more than 40 data, it is not the highest time. Although the refrigerator is always on, its electricity cost is not very high, so I record it as 10 minutes each time to avoid some errors that disrupt my life habits reflected by recording electrical appliances. The lowest is the vacuum cleaner because I live alone, and the carpet is rarely dirty or has garbage, so I basically clean it once or twice a week.

The horizontal bar chart records the usage time of each appliance in my home. Computers and TVs are the longest.

📦Variation in Usage Time by Period

The median line of afternoon is the highest and the box is the longest, which shows that I use electrical appliances the most in the afternoon, and the time spent using electrical appliances varies greatly. This means that although I stay at home in the afternoon, I sometimes do not use electrical appliances, perhaps because I am taking a nap or going out. Evening is the second, and its changes are not very big, which means that my living habits do not change often in the evening, and I often use fixed electrical appliances. Midnight is the shortest and the difference is stable. I sleep most of the time, so my habit of staying up late is not very serious. Although evening does not use electrical appliances as long as afternoon, the difference is large, because in the evening, I sometimes use appliances that are not often used, such as washing machines.

The box plot shows the distribution of total usage time in each time period. This helps to understand the distribution and central tendency of appliance usage in different time periods.
